examples.en: It is his Italian accent that distinguishes him.
The singer's voice is what distinguishes the band.
The only thing that distinguishes the dogs is their bark.
His modesty distinguishes him from his peers.
Man is gifted with a moral sense by which he distinguishes good from evil.
That easy swim of movement which distinguishes the ladies of this country.
The factor that distinguishes this company from the competition is customer service.
Accent is the elevation of the voice which distinguishes one part of a word from another.
